    public class VmtiHorizontalFieldOfView
extends VmtiFieldOfView

    Horizontal Field Of View (ST0903 VMTI Local Set Item 11 and VTrackItem Pack Item 22).

    From ST0903:

    Horizontal field of view of imaging sensor input to the VMTI process. Required only if VMTI process operates on an imaging sensor different than that described by the parent MISB ST 0601 LS; otherwise, the ST 0601 LS provides its Tag 16 â€“ HFOV value. Can use HFOV (Tag 16) from ST 0601 to scale VMTI column, row coordinates.

    Valid Values: The set of real numbers from 0 to 180 inclusive.

      • VmtiHorizontalFieldOfView

        public VmtiHorizontalFieldOfView(byte[] bytes,
                                 EncodingMode encodingMode)
        Create from encoded bytes.

        ST0903 changed the encoding to 2-byte IMAPB in ST0903.4. Earlier versions used a two-byte unsigned integer structure in the range [0, 2^16-1]that was then mapped into the range [0, 180.0] degrees. Which formatting applies can only be determined from the ST0903 version in this VmtiLocalSet. The compatibilityMode parameter determines whether to parse using the legacy encoding or current encoding.

        Note that this only affects parsing. Output encoding is always IMAPB (ST0903.4 or later).

        Parameters:
        bytes - Encoded byte array
        encodingMode - which encoding mode the bytes parameter uses.
